Golf Yankee Six is a movement dedicated to creating awareness of Veteran’s mental health and finding help for Veterans’ struggling with depression, PTSD, and suicide. GYS was created to encourage, educate, and invest directly into mental health services for our Veterans.
Florida is the third largest population in the nation after California and Texas with roughly 1.5 million Veterans.
69,000 active duty military personally reside in Florida, the 6th largest population in the nation.
The three most common mental health concerns for Veterans are Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD), depression and Traumatic Brain Injury (TBI).

section_title: Veterans more susceptible to mental health concerns
section_text: The rate of major depression among Veterans is 5x as high as civilians, while the rate of PTSD is nearly 15x higher.
GYS is here to serve our service members by supporting them, their families, and friends with tools and resources to assist in transitioning our heroes home
Monthly Events, educational resources, partnered perks, and much more to come for our heroes to get the help and support they need to effectively transition home from their service.
Our greatest allies in successfully helping truly make our heroes feel at home again. We will provide tools and resources in order to help you navigate the process of supporting a Veteran in need.

GYS wants to mobilize community members to participate in helping Veterans address their war within when they come back home. We want Veterans to see the size of our team when they look around the room and see Golf Yankee Six shirts. We want them to see shirts in the grocery store, at their local breweries, and where they receive mental health services. By purchasing our shirts, you can help us invest directly into the mental health services our Veterans deserve.

section_subtitle: To SAY and SHOW, we Golf Yankee Six.
section_text: Golf Yankee Six is a movement dedicated to creating awareness of Veteran’s mental health and finding help for Veterans’ struggling with depression, PTSD, and suicide in Orlando, Florida. We started to encourage, educate, and invest directly into mental health services for our Veterans. Use your voice to start a conversation, create hope, and show your support for our Veterans. If you want to support our mission, you can get involved by following us on Facebook and Instagram, attending our events, buying our American-made merchandise, or sharing resources from our website with a loved one.

We are two women with a goal to change the mental health world, specifically for our service men and women. As mental health practitioners, with 30 years combined experience and 15 years of friendship, we knew we could make a difference. We specialize in trauma, Post-traumatic Stress Disorder, and Veterans returning from combat. We have a specific passion to change the lives of our Veterans, one soldier at a time. What they see and experience is our motivation to never give up on them. Ever.
We hold these near and dear to our hearts

section_subtitle: An American company helping support the American people
section_text: We only use 100% American manufactured and designed products with US cotton. Some other companies use US cotton, but are made elsewhere. We are committed to only using fully American made products. We use Bayside - The American Made Tee - at https://usabayside.com/. Our shirts are printed by Breaking Free Industries https://breakingfreeindustries.com/ in California. About 3% of garments in the US are American made. This makes our American made products more expensive, but we stand behind our product choices by keeping everything we do locally.
